    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/prior-studies-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:Evidence",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior pedicle screw FEA validation studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of prior pedicle screw finite element modeling and validation studies spanning 2005–2020, including work from Rohlmann, Zander, Goel, and Patel research groups. This synthesis establishes the modeling assumptions for contact formulation, bone-screw interface behavior, and UHMWPE block material representation that were adopted in the present FEA ensemble. The synthesis demonstrates broad literature consensus that linear-elastic FEA with surface-to-surface contact reproduces F1717 construct behavior within 8% for a range of screw geometries and materials."
    },
